1
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:10,462
Um... uh, Sato-san?

2
00:00:10,963 --> 00:00:13,843
Th... this important talk you wanted...
what's it about?

3
00:00:14,011 --> 00:00:17,267
Just get in.
Y-yes!

4
00:00:21,734 --> 00:00:25,575
Huh? Wait a second...
this feels familiar somehow.

5
00:00:26,369 --> 00:00:29,750
That's right, that one time
when I opened the car door...

6
00:00:31,087 --> 00:00:33,258
Whoa! Aah...

7
00:00:33,717 --> 00:00:39,186
Ahahaha! Gotcha!
Gotcha! Ahahaha!

8
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:42,443
That time, Sato-san
got a real kick out of it.

9
00:00:43,361 --> 00:00:44,613
Whew.

10
00:00:44,697 --> 00:00:48,371
Well then, guess I'll let her
prank me good and proper today too.

11
00:00:48,705 --> 00:00:52,964
Whoa, please don't,
not one of these pranks!

12
00:00:53,923 --> 00:00:56,345
Huh...? Wait, what?

13
00:00:57,014 --> 00:00:59,185
What are you doing?
Huh?

14
00:00:59,643 --> 00:01:04,403
Oh... no, I just figured
this was another prank.

15
00:01:04,612 --> 00:01:06,574
I told you, it's something important.

16
00:01:06,992 --> 00:01:11,375
But last time you said it was
important too, and you got me.

17
00:01:13,546 --> 00:01:15,509
Hey.
Yes?

18
00:01:17,679 --> 00:01:18,890
Can't you tell just by looking?

19
00:01:19,141 --> 00:01:22,606
Uh, well, even if you tell me to look...

20
00:01:22,898 --> 00:01:25,862
all I can really say is
you're as beautiful as ever.

21
00:01:26,155 --> 00:01:28,743
What kind of nonsense is that? Honestly.

22
00:01:29,578 --> 00:01:31,707
S-so... what is it, then?

23
00:01:35,757 --> 00:01:38,221
It hasn't come. That.

24
00:01:38,805 --> 00:01:42,479
Huh. So "that" hasn't come.

25
00:01:44,108 --> 00:01:46,737
Hm? W-w-wait...
"hasn't come"... you don't mean...

26
00:01:47,239 --> 00:01:50,412
This is embarrassing,
so don't tell anyone, okay?

27
00:01:50,787 --> 00:01:52,416
Y-yes, of course.

28
00:01:52,708 --> 00:01:57,634
Ahh, but what do we do?
This is a matter of responsibility, isn't it?

29
00:02:00,265 --> 00:02:01,642
R-responsibility...

30
00:02:01,726 --> 00:02:04,189
I'll properly take...
Takagi-kun.

31
00:02:04,941 --> 00:02:08,573
Wait. A marriage between two
police officers...

32
00:02:08,781 --> 00:02:11,871
and in the same department,
no less...

33
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:16,339
Right, when a married couple works together,
to avoid potential complications...

34
00:02:16,422 --> 00:02:18,676
one of them gets
transferred, doesn't it?

35
00:02:19,178 --> 00:02:22,559
Sato-san is the flower of
Division One, and if she got transferred...

36
00:02:24,855 --> 00:02:28,071
who knows what the senior
detectives would do to me.

37
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:32,871
Which means I'd be the one
transferred to some other precinct.

38
00:02:32,956 --> 00:02:37,214
No, no, the noble thing would be
for me to quit and become a stay-at-home dad...

39
00:02:37,297 --> 00:02:39,093
Yes, understood.
Huh?

40
00:02:39,593 --> 00:02:40,887
We'll head over right away.

41
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:44,770
A sighting of the suspect
we've been searching for, in Beika-cho.

42
00:02:45,021 --> 00:02:46,774
We're heading straight to the scene.

43
00:02:47,109 --> 00:02:48,946
Ah... y-yes!

44
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:58,631
M-Miwako's having a baby!

45
00:02:58,715 --> 00:03:00,802
Congratulations are in order!

46
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:04,810
The sun blazing down,
undaunted by the heat...

47
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:06,480
a stylish and dashing
mystery show.

48
00:03:06,564 --> 00:03:09,988
Sato finally confesses to Takagi?
A perfect alibi and the riddle of flower meanings.

49
00:03:10,739 --> 00:03:11,992
Seeing through to the one and only truth...

50
00:03:12,075 --> 00:03:13,911
Looks like a kid, mind of an adult...

51
00:03:13,996 --> 00:03:16,500
His name is Detective Conan!

52
00:03:16,584 --> 00:03:21,927
♪~

53
00:04:50,146 --> 00:04:56,158
~♪

54
00:05:00,595 --> 00:05:05,795
"Detective Love Story at MPD Headquarters (Confession)"

55
00:05:05,795 --> 00:05:05,802
(cicadas chirping)

56
00:05:08,323 --> 00:05:12,373
(three of them yawning)

57
00:05:13,543 --> 00:05:17,049
Hey, hey, all three of you
yawning at once?

58
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:19,137
You're not Haibara, you know.

59
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,892
Well, excuse me for being the yawning girl.

60
00:05:22,143 --> 00:05:23,270
But...

61
00:05:23,353 --> 00:05:26,902
That new game
"Titan Hunter" is just so much fun...

62
00:05:26,986 --> 00:05:28,906
I couldn't help getting hooked on it.

63
00:05:29,157 --> 00:05:32,581
Sheesh. You're gonna waste
your whole summer break on a game?

64
00:05:32,664 --> 00:05:33,916
Ehehe.

65
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:38,426
Oh yeah, Ayumi got her dad
to help, and I'm at rank five!

66
00:05:38,676 --> 00:05:39,928
Seriously?

67
00:05:40,012 --> 00:05:43,561
I keep getting eaten
by the blue giant over and over...

68
00:05:43,644 --> 00:05:45,105
What kind of game is that?

69
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:49,238
Apparently it's a role-playing game
where you defend your own castle...

70
00:05:49,322 --> 00:05:51,577
from a race of giants
that come attacking you.

71
00:05:51,952 --> 00:05:53,371
Huh.

72
00:05:53,790 --> 00:05:57,506
Come to think of it, the strategy guide
comes out today, doesn't it?

73
00:05:57,589 --> 00:05:58,758
That's right.

74
00:05:58,841 --> 00:06:01,931
Hey, you think they're selling it
at the convenience store over there?

75
00:06:02,014 --> 00:06:03,183
Let's go check!

76
00:06:03,476 --> 00:06:08,026
Hey, you guys, weren't we
supposed to play soccer at the park?

77
00:06:09,446 --> 00:06:11,074
Nothing for it, I guess.

78
00:06:11,157 --> 00:06:13,412
Sheesh, honestly... hm?

79
00:06:15,082 --> 00:06:17,211
Was there an accident over there or something?

80
00:06:18,338 --> 00:06:19,925
But for that, those flowers...

81
00:06:20,718 --> 00:06:23,474
If I remember right, that's an obedient plant.

82
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:25,018
The flower meaning is...

83
00:06:25,102 --> 00:06:26,689
Hey, Edogawa-kun?
Ah!

84
00:06:27,314 --> 00:06:30,028
What are you doing?
We're leaving you behind.

85
00:06:30,112 --> 00:06:31,407
O-okay.

86
00:06:37,293 --> 00:06:39,088
Man, what a surprise that was.

87
00:06:39,756 --> 00:06:42,344
To think there'd be a complete
stranger who looks so much like him.

88
00:06:42,429 --> 00:06:44,098
Yeah, you're right.

89
00:06:45,685 --> 00:06:47,606
We're running a little late, but...

90
00:06:47,689 --> 00:06:50,612
want to grab lunch around here?
Ah, sure.

91
00:06:51,154 --> 00:06:53,618
Oh! Then maybe something sour?

92
00:06:54,118 --> 00:06:56,582
Huh? Why?

93
00:06:57,041 --> 00:07:01,007
Whoa, that's amazing, the Overlord Blade!

94
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:04,890
So cool!
"Attack power over 10,000..."

95
00:07:04,973 --> 00:07:09,483
"the one and only holy sword
feared by the giants," it says here!

96
00:07:09,566 --> 00:07:10,610
(Haibara yawning)

97
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:14,158
But it's a black-and-white photo,
so we can't tell the colors.

98
00:07:14,241 --> 00:07:19,126
You can't get it unless you beat the
super-huge red giant at rank eight, you know.

99
00:07:19,210 --> 00:07:21,548
Sounds like it'll take a while yet.

100
00:07:21,632 --> 00:07:24,388
I've got that sword.
Huh?!

101
00:07:25,055 --> 00:07:26,307
The hilt is shiny gold...

102
00:07:26,392 --> 00:07:28,521
and the pattern on the blade is red.

103
00:07:28,729 --> 00:07:30,065
After this you have to keep...

104
00:07:30,148 --> 00:07:31,694
collecting lots of...

105
00:07:31,777 --> 00:07:32,779
upgrade items...

106
00:07:32,862 --> 00:07:34,449
to forge the sword,
apparently, though.

107
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:38,373
Wow, so that means
you reached rank eight!

108
00:07:38,457 --> 00:07:39,459
Yeah.

109
00:07:39,543 --> 00:07:41,964
Hey, aren't you that kid
from the class next door...

110
00:07:42,047 --> 00:07:44,845
You're not showing off
and lying, are you?

111
00:07:45,053 --> 00:07:46,390
It's not a lie.

112
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:49,563
Hey, Toshinari nii-chan.
Yeah.

113
00:07:50,690 --> 00:07:53,111
You worked hard, Noriya.
Yeah.

114
00:07:53,571 --> 00:07:55,908
Huh? This guy from earlier...

115
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,458
If you really got the Overlord Blade,
I'd love to see it.

116
00:07:59,541 --> 00:08:01,712
Me too!
Me too!

117
00:08:01,795 --> 00:08:04,634
Then do you all want to come
to Toshinari nii-chan's place?

118
00:08:05,052 --> 00:08:06,722
Hey, that's okay, right?

119
00:08:06,805 --> 00:08:09,351
Toshinari nii-chan?
Hmm...

120
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:12,442
All right, go on ahead
and get in the car.

121
00:08:12,525 --> 00:08:14,111
I'll go pay for this.

122
00:08:14,529 --> 00:08:19,498
That comes to 1,350 yen.
Card, please.

123
00:08:19,915 --> 00:08:22,796
Sure. How would you like to pay?
One payment.

124
00:08:23,338 --> 00:08:24,633
Understood.

125
00:08:24,716 --> 00:08:27,472
Foreign car keys and a platinum card.

126
00:08:27,555 --> 00:08:29,308
Some rich kid, maybe?

127
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:35,530
Ugh.

128
00:08:35,947 --> 00:08:38,326
What a run-down apartment.

129
00:08:38,410 --> 00:08:39,788
Hey, Genta-kun!

130
00:08:39,871 --> 00:08:43,462
Hahaha, it looks shabby,
but home is where you make it.

131
00:08:43,921 --> 00:08:45,633
Well, I'll go park the car...

132
00:08:45,716 --> 00:08:47,762
so head on into the room.
Yeah.

133
00:08:53,566 --> 00:08:54,568
Whoa!

134
00:08:54,651 --> 00:08:56,738
It really is the Overlord Blade!

135
00:08:56,822 --> 00:08:59,076
The grip really is all shiny.

136
00:08:59,494 --> 00:09:02,584
Wow!
That's great!

137
00:09:03,460 --> 00:09:06,174
Sheesh, the trash bag is...

138
00:09:06,257 --> 00:09:10,265
full of snacks, cup noodles,
and convenience store bento containers.

139
00:09:11,810 --> 00:09:14,148
You can really see his diet.

140
00:09:14,315 --> 00:09:16,403
Hey, Haibara.
What?

141
00:09:17,572 --> 00:09:19,200
Didn't you smell something?

142
00:09:19,283 --> 00:09:23,500
Not really. Doesn't seem
like there's any food garbage in here.

143
00:09:23,751 --> 00:09:26,381
No, I mean out in the hallway,
before we came into this room.

144
00:09:26,882 --> 00:09:29,471
Hm, I didn't notice anything.

145
00:09:29,554 --> 00:09:31,600
I see. Hm?

146
00:09:39,741 --> 00:09:43,331
Hey, what are you doing,
rummaging through someone's house?

147
00:09:43,832 --> 00:09:45,503
Hey, Noriya-kun.
Hm?

148
00:09:46,672 --> 00:09:49,552
Did your big brother just
move into this place?

149
00:09:49,636 --> 00:09:52,934
No, it was about a month ago.

150
00:09:53,017 --> 00:09:56,357
Before summer break he lived in
the same building as me.

151
00:09:56,441 --> 00:09:57,443
Huh.

152
00:09:58,069 --> 00:10:02,412
And Toshinari nii-chan isn't
my brother, he's my cousin.

153
00:10:02,704 --> 00:10:04,958
He's my mom's older sister's kid.

154
00:10:05,626 --> 00:10:09,384
Right now my dad's away
on a business trip overseas...

155
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:12,598
and my mom went to take care of him
for a week...

156
00:10:12,682 --> 00:10:16,272
so just for that time I'm staying over
at Toshinari nii-chan's place.

157
00:10:16,355 --> 00:10:17,984
A whole week here?

158
00:10:18,276 --> 00:10:19,278
Yeah.

159
00:10:19,361 --> 00:10:22,452
Besides, my mom asked me to.

160
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:27,545
Toshinari nii-chan's big sister
died in a car accident half a year ago...

161
00:10:27,628 --> 00:10:30,050
and he was really down about it...

162
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:34,517
so she told me to stay with him
and cheer him up.

163
00:10:35,143 --> 00:10:37,189
Then those flowers from earlier...

164
00:10:37,272 --> 00:10:39,360
were at the site of that sister's accident.

165
00:10:39,778 --> 00:10:43,786
Oh yeah, he showed me a
photo of that sister before.

166
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:49,714
She was a kind sister who
often took us camping.

167
00:10:50,173 --> 00:10:54,098
Huh? Were there
this many photos before?

168
00:10:54,264 --> 00:10:57,270
Hey, let me see that.
U-uh, sure.

169
00:11:02,072 --> 00:11:05,161
That's strange, these last few photos...

170
00:11:05,830 --> 00:11:08,877
in every single one,
her eyes aren't looking this way.

171
00:11:10,423 --> 00:11:11,591
And what's this?

172
00:11:12,175 --> 00:11:14,848
There's a tiny hole
near the top of the photos.

173
00:11:17,437 --> 00:11:18,522
Ah!

174
00:11:19,983 --> 00:11:22,028
Th-that's Toshinari nii-chan's voice.

175
00:11:22,405 --> 00:11:24,701
The hallway... don't tell me...

176
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,667
Room four next door, huh.

177
00:11:33,552 --> 00:11:35,346
It's for sure that smell from before.

178
00:11:35,431 --> 00:11:37,894
C-Conan-kun...

179
00:11:38,562 --> 00:11:41,526
What on earth happened?
You guys, don't come in.

180
00:11:41,985 --> 00:11:46,453
Haibara, call the police.
Tell them someone's died here.

181
00:11:46,536 --> 00:11:48,247
Huh?!
Right, got it.

182
00:11:56,263 --> 00:11:57,558
What's that?

183
00:12:01,942 --> 00:12:04,029
The photos pinned to this board...

184
00:12:04,864 --> 00:12:07,411
the sun-fade marks and the photos
are slightly out of alignment.

185
00:12:08,872 --> 00:12:11,503
And it's not just one or two of them.

186
00:12:12,421 --> 00:12:13,757
Why would this be...

187
00:12:16,555 --> 00:12:19,852
In every single one,
her eyes aren't looking this way.

188
00:12:21,982 --> 00:12:24,529
There's a tiny hole
near the top of the photos.

189
00:12:27,284 --> 00:12:28,495
Don't tell me.

190
00:12:29,497 --> 00:12:31,793
The one who did this...

191
00:12:33,422 --> 00:12:34,674
don't tell me...

192
00:12:45,888 --> 00:12:47,933
Still, man...

193
00:12:48,017 --> 00:12:50,814
to think those two
had gotten that far.

194
00:12:50,898 --> 00:12:53,235
That settles it, they're tying the knot!

195
00:12:53,445 --> 00:12:56,534
But man, this is bad, Takagi-kun.

196
00:12:56,618 --> 00:12:58,371
Huh? Bad how?

197
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:02,170
I mean, just imagine if the
other detectives found out about this.

198
00:13:02,421 --> 00:13:04,842
Ah, true.

199
00:13:04,926 --> 00:13:07,347
Sato-san sure has
a lot of fans.

200
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:10,979
It's bad, seriously bad.
It really is.

201
00:13:11,981 --> 00:13:15,196
Seriously, this is bad.
Hm? Whoa!

202
00:13:16,198 --> 00:13:19,747
U-um, Yumi-san?
Hm?

203
00:13:20,081 --> 00:13:22,712
Your words and your expression
don't match at all.

204
00:13:22,795 --> 00:13:23,964
Huh?

205
00:13:25,801 --> 00:13:26,970
The victim was...

206
00:13:27,053 --> 00:13:31,270
Yasutomi Hiroto, 31, a freelancer.

207
00:13:31,646 --> 00:13:35,278
According to the coroner's assessment,
the estimated time of death...

208
00:13:35,361 --> 00:13:38,117
was between 7 and 9 last night.

209
00:13:39,537 --> 00:13:41,416
Stabbed repeatedly in the chest and abdomen.

210
00:13:42,083 --> 00:13:47,470
And the one who first discovered the body
was the resident next door to this room...

211
00:13:47,553 --> 00:13:50,934
Shiga Toshinari-san, correct?
Yes.

212
00:13:51,561 --> 00:13:56,236
After I parked my car in the lot
and was heading back to my room...

213
00:13:56,403 --> 00:13:58,450
there was a strange smell
coming from this room.

214
00:13:58,909 --> 00:14:03,125
The door was unlocked, so when
I opened it, I found this scene.

215
00:14:03,209 --> 00:14:08,678
I was surprised when this kid who's a friend of my cousin Noriya, 
just went into the room without asking.

216
00:14:09,346 --> 00:14:10,849
It's Conan-kun.

217
00:14:11,935 --> 00:14:14,607
Then the girl who called it in...

218
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:15,692
That was me.

219
00:14:16,235 --> 00:14:18,615
Today everyone came to visit...

220
00:14:18,698 --> 00:14:21,119
the room of Noriya-kun's cousin.

221
00:14:21,830 --> 00:14:26,004
But you're quite the Grim Reaper,
right up there with Mouri-san.

222
00:14:26,088 --> 00:14:29,595
A murder scene every single time.
Ehehehe.

223
00:14:29,679 --> 00:14:32,893
B-but you detectives
got here pretty fast too, didn't you?

224
00:14:33,227 --> 00:14:36,693
Yeah, we got a tip that a clerk
at a flower shop fairly close to here...

225
00:14:36,776 --> 00:14:40,241
resembled the suspect
we've been looking for.

226
00:14:40,534 --> 00:14:43,038
Turned out to be a total stranger, though.

227
00:14:43,122 --> 00:14:45,544
We happened to be in the neighborhood...

228
00:14:45,627 --> 00:14:48,425
so we got called in to this scene.

229
00:14:48,925 --> 00:14:51,848
Well, if Takagi-kun
hadn't been off...

230
00:14:51,931 --> 00:14:55,229
whispering about flowers with that clerk,
we could've left right away.

231
00:14:55,313 --> 00:14:58,945
No, the reason we lingered around here
was because we were having lunch, right?

232
00:14:59,362 --> 00:15:01,283
You were talking about flowers?

233
00:15:01,366 --> 00:15:02,870
Are you giving them to someone?

234
00:15:02,953 --> 00:15:05,959
But you wouldn't have to whisper
if it were Detective Sato, right?

235
00:15:06,376 --> 00:15:07,463
An affair.

236
00:15:08,005 --> 00:15:09,382
Oh! You think so too?

237
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:11,345
N-no, that's not it!

238
00:15:11,429 --> 00:15:14,142
Hey, never mind all that...

239
00:15:14,225 --> 00:15:16,648
if the victim died between
7 and 9 last night...

240
00:15:16,731 --> 00:15:19,654
why not ask Noriya-kun
or Toshinari-san?

241
00:15:19,862 --> 00:15:21,449
If they were in the room next door...

242
00:15:21,532 --> 00:15:24,329
they might have heard
some suspicious sounds.

243
00:15:24,747 --> 00:15:28,922
Around that time last night, I was
watching TV with Toshinari nii-chan.

244
00:15:29,005 --> 00:15:31,469
The "Kamen Yaiba" movie was on.

245
00:15:31,928 --> 00:15:34,349
Oh! Ayumi watched that too!

246
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,606
Me too! It was super fun, right?

247
00:15:37,690 --> 00:15:41,489
If I recall, it ran from 7 to 9,
its TV premiere.

248
00:15:41,948 --> 00:15:45,329
And while you were watching it,
did you hear any strange sounds...

249
00:15:45,414 --> 00:15:48,002
like a groan, anything?
Yeah.

250
00:15:48,085 --> 00:15:51,299
Partway through, that man next door
banged on the door...

251
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:53,262
and yelled at us to keep it down.

252
00:15:53,805 --> 00:15:55,809
What time was that, around?

253
00:15:55,892 --> 00:15:59,232
I think it was probably around 7:30.

254
00:15:59,315 --> 00:16:03,240
I apologized through the door
and turned the volume down, though.

255
00:16:03,825 --> 00:16:08,250
So at that point, Yasutomi-san
was still alive, then.

256
00:16:08,710 --> 00:16:11,674
Any odd sounds after that?
Not that I noticed.

257
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:14,513
"Kamen Yaiba" is a hero show...

258
00:16:14,597 --> 00:16:18,353
so there were people screaming
and explosions going off constantly...

259
00:16:18,521 --> 00:16:21,819
so even if there'd been a suspicious sound,
I might not have noticed.

260
00:16:21,903 --> 00:16:22,988
Besides...

261
00:16:23,072 --> 00:16:26,328
the neighbor's body is at
the kitchen sink...

262
00:16:26,412 --> 00:16:30,670
two rooms away from where
we were watching TV.

263
00:16:31,506 --> 00:16:36,139
Come to think of it, I saw the neighbor
at the convenience store yesterday evening.

264
00:16:36,223 --> 00:16:38,478
What time was that, around?

265
00:16:38,561 --> 00:16:42,820
Hmm, it was while I was
buying a bento for dinner.

266
00:16:43,153 --> 00:16:45,492
I was worried about
the bento's expiration date...

267
00:16:45,575 --> 00:16:48,790
so I remember asking Noriya
what day it was.

268
00:16:48,873 --> 00:16:50,334
You asked a child the date?

269
00:16:50,710 --> 00:16:53,842
Yeah, I was holding the shopping basket...

270
00:16:54,342 --> 00:16:57,599
and the newspaper he bought at the
store that day was in it...

271
00:16:57,683 --> 00:17:01,691
so I told him it said "August 13th" on it.

272
00:17:01,774 --> 00:17:04,362
I said, "It's the day the Yaiba
movie's on TV."

273
00:17:04,613 --> 00:17:07,411
If it was the 13th, then yes,
that was yesterday.

274
00:17:07,494 --> 00:17:11,293
At that time, was Yasutomi-san
with anyone?

275
00:17:11,586 --> 00:17:14,340
No, I believe he was alone.

276
00:17:14,925 --> 00:17:18,892
Hey, Noriya-kun, while you were
watching the Yaiba movie...

277
00:17:18,975 --> 00:17:21,647
did Toshinari-san get up
to use the bathroom or anything?

278
00:17:21,731 --> 00:17:26,072
No. I was leaning against
Toshinari nii-chan the whole time we watched.

279
00:17:26,574 --> 00:17:28,703
What did you do after it ended?

280
00:17:28,786 --> 00:17:31,459
That movie ended a little
before 9, right?

281
00:17:31,542 --> 00:17:34,339
Yeah. As soon as it ended
I went to pee...

282
00:17:34,423 --> 00:17:36,092
and then went back to the game.

283
00:17:36,427 --> 00:17:39,725
"Back to" it means
you were playing before that too?

284
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:44,860
Yeah, the whole time from when we got back
from the store until the movie started.

285
00:17:44,944 --> 00:17:48,075
Then Toshinari nii-chan
looked at his watch...

286
00:17:48,158 --> 00:17:52,501
and said, "Uh-oh, it's already 7,
the movie's starting, let's save."

287
00:17:52,584 --> 00:17:56,884
So I hurried up, saved the game,
and switched back to the TV...

288
00:17:56,968 --> 00:18:00,015
and it was just barely in time,
right as the movie was starting.

289
00:18:00,475 --> 00:18:04,441
Then after the movie ended,
while you were in the bathroom...

290
00:18:04,525 --> 00:18:06,946
did Toshinari-san leave the room at all?

291
00:18:07,238 --> 00:18:08,950
No, from outside the bathroom...

292
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:11,455
he was asking me what snacks
I wanted to eat.

293
00:18:11,872 --> 00:18:14,878
And after that, you two
just kept playing the game?

294
00:18:14,962 --> 00:18:16,047
That's right.

295
00:18:16,131 --> 00:18:18,051
We played pretty late into the night...

296
00:18:18,135 --> 00:18:21,141
woke up early and played some more...

297
00:18:21,224 --> 00:18:24,982
then went to the store with Toshinari
nii-chan to buy breakfast...

298
00:18:25,065 --> 00:18:28,405
and after that we played
until around noon...

299
00:18:28,489 --> 00:18:31,202
but I got sleepy, so I took a nap...

300
00:18:31,537 --> 00:18:33,541
and after I woke up I played again...

301
00:18:33,624 --> 00:18:37,214
and then I got hungry, so we went
to the store again just now...

302
00:18:37,591 --> 00:18:39,762
and that's where we ran into you guys.

303
00:18:39,845 --> 00:18:42,183
N-nothing but games, huh.

304
00:18:42,266 --> 00:18:44,480
No wonder your rank was so high.

305
00:18:44,563 --> 00:18:45,899
I'm jealous!

306
00:18:45,982 --> 00:18:48,738
...So, what did you
do about lunch?

307
00:18:49,072 --> 00:18:52,871
Oh, I was eating snacks,
so I didn't get hungry at all.

308
00:18:52,954 --> 00:18:55,334
Eating snacks and playing
games the whole time...

309
00:18:55,418 --> 00:18:56,587
Lucky.

310
00:18:56,670 --> 00:18:59,927
Sounds like heaven.
Don't go imitating him.

311
00:19:01,012 --> 00:19:04,978
So today too, were you with
Toshinari-san the whole time?

312
00:19:05,062 --> 00:19:09,112
Hmm, after we ate breakfast,
he said he had something to take care of...

313
00:19:09,195 --> 00:19:11,450
told me to be good and play games,
and went out.

314
00:19:12,076 --> 00:19:15,124
He said it'd be bad if the man next door
got mad at us again...

315
00:19:15,207 --> 00:19:17,587
so he told me to wear headphones
while I played.

316
00:19:18,130 --> 00:19:21,302
What time was that, around?
Um, let's see...

317
00:19:22,012 --> 00:19:24,267
We went to the store to buy
breakfast...

318
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:26,062
at around 6 in the morning...

319
00:19:26,146 --> 00:19:30,613
and he left right after we got home and ate,
so I think it was around 7.

320
00:19:30,864 --> 00:19:33,411
The clock behind the
store clerk...

321
00:19:33,494 --> 00:19:35,748
said it was a little past 6, too.

322
00:19:37,878 --> 00:19:41,217
What?
Don't tell me you suspect that man?

323
00:19:41,301 --> 00:19:43,598
Hm...
U-um...

324
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:47,229
Is it about time I head
back to my own room?

325
00:19:47,313 --> 00:19:51,029
I don't want the children
near the body any longer.

326
00:19:51,112 --> 00:19:52,114
You're right.

327
00:19:52,824 --> 00:19:56,206
Just to be safe, I'd like
to check the contents...

328
00:19:56,289 --> 00:19:58,753
of your trash bag, if that's okay?

329
00:19:58,836 --> 00:20:00,590
Sure, I don't mind.

330
00:20:00,673 --> 00:20:03,220
Ah, from behind like that...
Huh?

331
00:20:03,554 --> 00:20:06,894
Weren't you the one who was
at the flower shop earlier?

332
00:20:06,977 --> 00:20:09,900
Ah, yes. I did buy some flowers.

333
00:20:10,234 --> 00:20:14,451
I knew it. At that flower shop,
when I asked the clerk...

334
00:20:14,535 --> 00:20:17,916
what would be a good flower to give
when a wish comes true...

335
00:20:17,999 --> 00:20:20,337
she suggested the obedient plant...

336
00:20:20,421 --> 00:20:23,469
that the customer just before me
had bought.

337
00:20:23,761 --> 00:20:27,561
And that's when I spotted you
leaving the shop.

338
00:20:27,769 --> 00:20:30,984
So, Detective Takagi,
something good happened to you?

339
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,904
Did you win a prize on an ice cream stick?

340
00:20:32,988 --> 00:20:34,365
Hey, hey, tell us!

341
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:38,039
Ah, no... please help me out here.

342
00:20:38,123 --> 00:20:39,918
Huh? Why?

343
00:20:40,002 --> 00:20:42,507
I told you I'd take
proper responsibility, didn't I?

344
00:20:42,591 --> 00:20:44,385
Oh, that?

345
00:20:44,928 --> 00:20:48,769
Well, you do bear part of
the responsibility...

346
00:20:49,145 --> 00:20:51,399
so it's only natural for you to take it.

347
00:20:52,944 --> 00:20:54,906
R-right.

348
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:58,371
Hey, mister, you bought
those flowers too, right?

349
00:20:58,456 --> 00:21:00,668
Yeah.
In that case...

350
00:21:01,629 --> 00:21:04,426
did a wish of yours come true too, mister?

351
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:08,434
Ah... yeah, something like that.

352
00:21:12,066 --> 00:21:15,364
All right, Shiga-san, shall we
head to your room?

353
00:21:15,448 --> 00:21:16,867
S-sure.

354
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:22,252
Hey, Detective Takagi.

355
00:21:22,336 --> 00:21:24,591
Huh? What is it, Conan-kun?

356
00:21:24,675 --> 00:21:26,804
There's something
I'd like you to look into.

357
00:21:26,887 --> 00:21:27,889
Huh?

358
00:21:28,139 --> 00:21:32,649
Toshinari-san was laying flowers
on the road in front of the flower shop...

359
00:21:32,732 --> 00:21:35,320
so I wondered if there'd been
an accident or something.

360
00:21:35,404 --> 00:21:36,699
I-I see.

361
00:21:36,782 --> 00:21:39,538
Come on, Takagi-kun, stop dawdling.

362
00:21:39,621 --> 00:21:41,207
Ah, right.

363
00:21:41,542 --> 00:21:43,462
Hurry up.
Wait, are you okay?

364
00:21:43,546 --> 00:21:45,758
Sato-san, you need to take it easy...

365
00:21:49,265 --> 00:21:52,772
The one who killed
Yasutomi-san is most likely him.

366
00:21:53,441 --> 00:21:55,987
It's got to be Shiga Toshinari-san.

367
00:21:57,239 --> 00:22:00,413
And I've probably got
the motive figured out too.

368
00:22:01,205 --> 00:22:03,711
But the problem is his alibi.

369
00:22:04,796 --> 00:22:10,307
During the time of the crime, the night of
August 13th, between 7 and 9...

370
00:22:11,810 --> 00:22:14,858
he has an alibi that he was
with Noriya-kun the whole time.

371
00:22:15,526 --> 00:22:21,329
Damn it. Just how exactly
did he kill Yasutomi-san?

372
00:22:24,461 --> 00:22:29,303
So? Takagi-kun,
did something good happen to you?

373
00:22:30,473 --> 00:22:31,642
Huh?

374
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:38,196
♪~

375
00:23:46,416 --> 00:23:51,760
~♪

376
00:23:54,056 --> 00:23:57,689
Wh-what's with
this ominous atmosphere?

377
00:24:00,026 --> 00:24:01,028
Actually...

378
00:24:01,571 --> 00:24:05,203
Sato-san's developed the awareness of a mother.

379
00:24:05,621 --> 00:24:08,376
Hey, that Yaiba movie
you watched last night...

380
00:24:08,877 --> 00:24:10,464
Yeah, that's right.

381
00:24:10,548 --> 00:24:13,679
I had to hold it in even though
I felt like I'd pee my pants.

382
00:24:14,304 --> 00:24:15,808
Just as I thought.

383
00:24:16,146 --> 00:24:17,446
Next Conan,

384
00:24:17,446 --> 00:24:21,346
"Detective Love Story at MPD Headquarters (Truth)"

385
00:24:36,946 --> 00:24:39,446
Next Conan's Hint:

386
00:24:39,446 --> 00:24:41,746
"Newspaper".

387
00:24:41,789 --> 00:24:43,293
Summer break is...
games...

388
00:24:43,376 --> 00:24:44,587
snacks... naps...

389
00:24:44,670 --> 00:24:46,173
Go play outside!
